** About the company **

We exist to grow our customer’s business through our people and technologies.

Worldsmart POS Solutions provide a complete retail ecosystem to our retailers.

We are a national business with offices across the country, and a large
national client base. At Worldsmart, we seek people who embody our core values
of Honesty, Accountability, Collaboration, and Innovation. We recognise that
our people are our biggest asset, and we create opportunities to help our team
build a genuine career

** Position overview **

We are looking for an individual looking to build a career with a market
leading technology company. We take pride in our proprietary software – which
has recently been re-engineered – to set Worldsmart up for future growth. More
importantly this allows our retailers the opportunity to drive further
efficiencies through new technologies, to help grow their business.

As a member of our team, you will report to the QLD State Manager and work
closely with our WorldSmart team to deliver high quality, value-add solutions
to our retailers. The primary focus is on providing the highest quality
Installation, Implementation, Training and Support services for our Point-of-
Sale(POS), E-Commerce and Loyalty products to our client base.

We are searching for a motivated individual who can handle responsibilities
both in a team environment and autonomously. Core responsibilities include;

  * Installation of POS hardware & software products to clients 
  * System trouble shooting and problem solving 
  * Customer training and support 
  * Pre sales support 

** About you **

Essential

  * Previous experience operating retail or hospitality POS (Grocery Manager or SmartRetail highly regarded) 
  * Commitment to honesty, accountability, collaboration, and innovation. 
  * Full & current driver’s license and ability to travel when required. 
  * Ability to communicate effectively, particularly verbally, with a wide range of clientele. 
  * Work effectively as a member of a team whilst at the same time   
possess the ability to make consistent, rational and independent decisions.

  * Ability to work effectively under pressure and with minimum supervision. 
  * Demonstratable skills in exemplary customer service. 
  * Advanced PC & Server configuration knowledge. 
  * Microsoft Network configuration 

Desirable

  * Technical knowledge of POS, computer systems and software (EFT, LAN would be beneficial) 
  * Experience in non-scripted support environment/non-traditional ICT role. 
  * Post-Secondary studies in Information Technology. 
  * Previous experience utilising computerised Back Office & POS systems   
within a retail environment, in particular the Grocery industry.

** What’s in it for you **

  * Part of a large family-owned business with genuine career paths. 
  * Attractive salary, plus super, car allowance, laptop & phone. 
  * Great comradery as part of a large and diverse team. 
  * Access to Employee Assistance Program. 

** How to apply **

Applications to be addressed to ** Ben Lam Sing – QLD State Manager ** .
Please ensure your application includes a cover letter addressing how you
align with our needs and values.

